# placeholder-img

Python client SDK for the [Placeholder Image API](https://placeholder-api.surge.sh). Generate and download placeholder images with a simple Pythonic API.

## Installation

```bash
pip install placeholder-img
```

## Usage

### Create a client

```python
from placeholder_img import PlaceholderClient

client = PlaceholderClient()
# With API key or custom base URL:
# client = PlaceholderClient(api_key="your-key", base_url="http://149.202.58.157:8892")
```

### Get a placeholder image URL

```python
url = client.url(300, 200)
# => "https://placeholder-api.surge.sh/300x200.png"

url = client.url(400, 300, bg_color="336699", text_color="ffffff", text="Hello!", format="jpg")
# => "https://placeholder-api.surge.sh/400x300.jpg?bg=336699&fg=ffffff&text=Hello!"
```

### Generate a PIL Image

```python
img = client.generate(300, 200, bg_color="cc0000")
img.show()
```

### Download and save to file

```python
client.download(300, 200, "placeholder.png")
client.download(400, 300, "photo.jpg", format="jpg", text="Demo")
```

## API

### `PlaceholderClient(api_key=None, base_url="https://placeholder-api.surge.sh")`

Creates a new client instance.

### `client.url(width, height, bg_color=None, text_color=None, text=None, format="png")`

Returns the URL string for the placeholder image.

### `client.generate(width, height, bg_color=None, text_color=None, text=None, format="png")`

Downloads the image and returns a `PIL.Image.Image` object.

### `client.download(width, height, filepath, bg_color=None, text_color=None, text=None, format="png")`

Downloads the image and saves it to `filepath`. Returns the file path.

